                                span For Marcelo Pollack, from the human rights NGO Amnesty International, echoed the concerns of impunity, calling it the “backbone of the human rights crisis in Colombia,” and noted that the “majority of the victims [of Colombia’s armed conflict] have not been identified, and even less [of the perpetrators] have been brought to justice.”#[br]
